<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="51" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="51">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="51">
The adult and genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authority="Moeschler, 1886" authorityName="Moeschler" authorityYear="1886" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Elasmia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" lsidName="Elasmia insularis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insularis">Elasmia insularis</taxonomicName>
were illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation author="Torre, SL" journalOrPublisher="Universidad de Oriente, Santiago de Cuba" pageId="8" pageNumber="59" title="Revision de las Notodontidae de Cuba, con la descripcion de dos nuevas especies." year="1959">Torre and Alayo (1959)</bibRefCitation>
. We examined male specimens, and their genitalia, of 
<taxonomicName authority="Moeschler, 1886" authorityName="Moeschler" authorityYear="1886" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Elasmia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" lsidName="Elasmia insularis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insularis">Elasmia insularis</taxonomicName>
from Cuba. 
<taxonomicName authority="Moeschler, 1886" authorityName="Moeschler" authorityYear="1886" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Elasmia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" lsidName="Elasmia insularis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insularis">Elasmia insularis</taxonomicName>
is not known to occur in Florida (
<bibRefCitation author="Heppner, JB" journalOrPublisher="Florida Department of Agriculture &amp; Consumer Services, Gainesville, Florida" pageId="8" pageNumber="59" title="Arthropods of Florida and Neighboring Land Areas Volume 17 Lepidoptera of Florida Part 1 Introduction and Catalog." year="2003">Heppner 2003</bibRefCitation>
), and it is doubtful that it occurs in the U.S. Inclusion of 
<taxonomicName authority="Moeschler, 1886" authorityName="Moeschler" authorityYear="1886" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Elasmia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" lsidName="Elasmia insularis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insularis">Elasmia insularis</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Lafontaine, JD" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="8" pageNumber="59" pagination="1 - 239" title="Annotated check list of the Noctuoidea (Insecta, Lepidoptera) of North America north of Mexico." url="doi: 10.3897/zookeys.40.414" volume="40" year="2010">Lafontaine and Schmidt (2010)</bibRefCitation>
was based on erroneous reports from Texas (
<bibRefCitation author="Knudson, EC" journalOrPublisher="Houston, Texas" pageId="8" pageNumber="59" title="Checklist of the Lepidoptera of Texas." year="1999">Knudson and Bordelon 1999</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
